The paper discusses the use of domain randomization for learning robust policies for robot systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as gradient-based search methods to learn the domain randomization distribution, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of context-conditioned policies, which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
